    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with a lid with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>and<strong> spinach</strong> to a<strong> sieve</strong> and place the sieve over the potatoes</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 12-15 min or until the potatoes and broccoli are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Combine the <strong>lemon zest</strong>, your <strong>cracked black pepper </strong>and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>on a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> lemon pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place your hand flat onto your <strong>chicken</strong> </p><p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p><p>Coat the <strong>chicken </strong>in the<strong> lemon pepper </strong>and tap off any excess \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil the kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Roll the <strong>zested</strong> <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once golden, reduce the temperature to medium and add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, then cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> Chinese rice wine </strong>with your<strong> clotted cream</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-12 min further or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy lemon & pepper chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lemon-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-mash-and-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Serve the <strong>creamy lemon & pepper chicken </strong>with the<strong> mash </strong>and the<strong> steamed broccoli & spinach </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
